article.headline: Lehigh 72, Navy 67
article.story: ANNAPOLIS, Md. (AP) -- Joe Knight scored 25 points to lead Lehigh to a 72-67 win over Navy on Saturday. Knight also had nine rebounds to go along with his season-high in points as the defending Patriot League champions got their third straight conference win. The Mountain Hawks (9-7) survived a scare from Navy, outscoring the Mids 7-2 over the final minute and a half. Navy (4-11) trailed 59-43 with 9:20 to play but outscored Lehigh 17-1 over the next five minutes to tie the game at 60-60 with 4:07 to play. Lehigh went back up 65-60, but Navy tied it again on a 3-point basket by Taj Mathews with 1:30 to play. Jose Olivero, who scored 10 points, had seven points in the final 2:22 for Lehigh, including a 3-pointer that put Lehigh up 65-60 and a pair of free throws with 1:17 to play which broke the final tie. He also hit two free throws with 22 seconds left to put Lehigh up 71-65. Navy shot just 37.5 percent from the floor, but staged its second half comeback around the 3-point shot. Mathews led Navy with 16 points and senior George O'Garro posted his first career double-double with 14 points and 10 rebounds. Jason Mgebroff finished with 12 points for the Hawks, including 10 in the first half. Lehigh led 38-33 at the half and scored the first six points of the second half to go ahead 44-33.
